workarounds.action: Pull and rebase: git pull --rebase origin <branch> then git push
workarounds.how: Replays your commits on top of remote changes

workarounds.action: Pull with merge: git pull origin <branch> then git push
workarounds.how: Creates a merge commit combining local and remote changes

frequently_confused_with.distinction: Both produce similar messages, but 'error-failed-to-push-some-refs' and 'local-changes-overwritten' differ in root cause and environment context.
'error' indicates a rejected Git push (remote has new commits), while 'Aborting commit due to empty commit message' indicates an aborted async operation.
